  "notes": "Need for Speed II uses straightforward visual communication typical of arcade racing paradigm: car selection, track selection, and opponent positioning convey game state. The game lacks narrative faction systems or political elements. Danger is communicated through track geometry and opponent proximity. Safety is implicit in clear track space. Environmental storytelling is minimal but present through country-themed track design and vehicle showcase system providing manufacturer and development context. The game emphasizes visual car diversity (eight real high-end sports cars with special edition variants) as primary identity differentiation. Graphics limitations noted by critics (pop-in, polygon models) reduce clarity of environmental storytelling potential.",
